Logging this issue since I don't have time to chase it down currently and there is a workaround we can use in the mean time.

When defining the API config section within a template and then having multiple neighbors inherit that template only one of those neighbors will pick up the api config. 

In our case we have a backend process which handles logging of outgoing routes using the following config:

api {
    processes [ logger ];
    send {
        update;
        packets;
    }
 }

When placed in a template to allow all neighbors to use the same api config we are only receiving route information from one neighbor. A workaround for this issue is to simply place the api config section in each neighbor definition which then seems to correctly send route information from each neighbor.

